---
/**
 * GPU memory hierarchy: Registers → Shared Memory → L2 → VRAM
 * Layered diagram with access times.
 */
---

<figure class="gpu-mem-hier">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 500 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="GPU memory hierarchy from registers to VRAM">
    <!-- Registers (innermost) -->
    <rect x="175" y="10" width="150" height="36" rx="6" class="tier tier-reg" />
    <text x="250" y="28" class="tier-label">Registers</text>
    <text x="250" y="40" class="tier-detail">Per thread · ~1 cycle · 256 KB/SM</text>

    <!-- Shared memory -->
    <rect x="120" y="56" width="260" height="36" rx="6" class="tier tier-smem" />
    <text x="250" y="74" class="tier-label">Shared Memory</text>
    <text x="250" y="86" class="tier-detail">Per block · ~5 cycles · 48–100 KB/SM · programmer-managed</text>

    <!-- L2 cache -->
    <rect x="70" y="102" width="360" height="36" rx="6" class="tier tier-l2" />
    <text x="250" y="120" class="tier-label">L2 Cache</text>
    <text x="250" y="132" class="tier-detail">Global · ~200 cycles · 4–50 MB · hardware-managed</text>

    <!-- VRAM -->
    <rect x="20" y="148" width="460" height="36" rx="6" class="tier tier-vram" />
    <text x="250" y="166" class="tier-label">VRAM (Global Memory)</text>
    <text x="250" y="178" class="tier-detail">Global · ~400 cycles · 8–80 GB · ~1–3 TB/s</text>

    <!-- Arrows showing speed gradient -->
    <text x="500" y="30" class="speed-label fast">⚡ Fastest</text>
    <text x="500" y="80" class="speed-label">&darr;</text>
    <text x="500" y="130" class="speed-label">&darr;</text>
    <text x="500" y="170" class="speed-label slow">🐢 Slowest</text>

    <!-- Size gradient -->
    <text x="0" y="30" class="size-label small">Smallest</text>
    <text x="0" y="80" class="size-label">&darr;</text>
    <text x="0" y="130" class="size-label">&darr;</text>
    <text x="0" y="170" class="size-label big">Largest</text>

    <!-- Key insight callout -->
    <rect x="85" y="194" width="330" height="22" rx="4" class="callout-box" />
    <text x="250" y="209" class="callout-text">Shared memory = programmable L1 cache (you manage it)</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>The GPU memory hierarchy mirrors the CPU's — keep hot data close to compute. The key difference: <strong>shared memory</strong> is explicitly managed by the programmer, unlike CPU caches.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .gpu-mem-hier {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .gpu-mem-hier svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 500px;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .gpu-mem-hier figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .tier {
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }
  .tier-reg { fill: #e8f5e9; stroke: #66bb6a; }
  .tier-smem { fill: #e3f2fd; stroke: #42a5f5; }
  .tier-l2 { fill: #fff8e1; stroke: #ffca28; }
  .tier-vram { fill: #fce4ec; stroke: #ef5350; }
  .tier-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #333;
  }
  .tier-detail {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 7.5px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #777;
  }
  .speed-label, .size-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    fill: #aaa;
  }
  .speed-label { text-anchor: start; }
  .size-label { text-anchor: end; }
  .speed-label.fast { fill: #2e7d32; }
  .speed-label.slow { fill: #c62828; }
  .size-label.small { fill: #888; }
  .size-label.big { fill: #888; }
  .callout-box {
    fill: #f3e5f5;
    stroke: #ba68c8;
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }
  .callout-text {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #7b1fa2;
  }
</style>
